     fetched and converted properly. Creating custom SVGs for geometry problems violates pedagogical accuracy requirements.
  2. The generated SVG is visually incorrect and poorly constructed:
     - The triangle representation looks malformed and unprofessional
     - The proportions and positioning are wrong
     - The dashed height line and labels are poorly placed
     - This low-quality visual would confuse students rather than help them understand the concept
  3. This demonstrates a critical failure mode where the AI attempts to "recreate" precise geometric figures instead
